cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.OO, cs.SD, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a methodology for software system modeling. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper explores the reconceptualization of objects, which is a fundamental concept in programming languages. 
- cs.OO (Object-Oriented Programming) is relevant as the paper compares the object-oriented approach with the proposed thing-oriented modeling. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is relevant as the paper discusses the analysis phase of software system modeling. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon how the proposed modeling methodology affects the interaction between humans and computers.
